Russia Leads Italy 2-0 in Fed Cup Semis; Belgium, Czech Republic Tied 1-1

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-04-16T16:53:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-16/russia-leads-italy-2-0-in-fed-cup-semis-belgium-czech-republic-tied-1-1.html
Russia  leads Italy 2-0 after the
first day of the Fed Cup tennis semifinals, while Belgium and
the  Czech Republic  are tied 1-1.  Vera Zvonareva beat Sara Errani 6-0, 6-2 and Svetlana
Kuznetsova defeated Roberta Vinci 6-2, 6-7 (4-7), 6-1 in Moscow
as Russia put two-time defending champion Italy on the brink of
elimination from women’s tennis’s top team competition.  Petra Kvitova beat Kirsten Flipkens 6-2, 7-6 (7-4) to give
the Czech Republic the lead in their semifinal in Charleroi,
Belgium, before Yanina Wickmayer drew the home side even with a
6-4, 6-4 win over Barbora Zahlavova Strycova.  Both semifinals conclude tomorrow with two reverse singles
matches, followed by a doubles match.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  